{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-andiamo-admin-login",
    "name": "Andiamo Admin Login API",
    "description": "Smoke tests for admin auth on collection variable `baseUrl`.\n\n**Manual login with real email/password in Postman**\n1. Set **`admin_email`**, **`admin_password`** (Secret), **`recaptcha_token`**. Prefer an **Environment** (top-right dropdown) so they override empty collection defaults; or edit collection **Variables**.\n2. Open **Chrome/Edge** → `https://www.andiamoevents.com/admin/login` → **F12** → **Network** → filter `admin-login`.\n3. Submit once (wrong password is fine) → **`admin-login`** → **Payload** → copy **`recaptchaToken`** only.\n4. Paste into **`recaptcha_token`**; send POST within **1–2 minutes**.\n5. Run **`POST … real credentials`**, then **`GET verify-admin`**.\n\n**Postman JSON:** The manual POST uses a **Pre-request** script: `JSON.stringify` plus variable resolution (**environment before collection** so empty collection placeholders do not hide your env secrets). You can also put real JSON in the Body tab; the script merges missing fields from parsed JSON.\n\n**Headers:** `Origin` = `{{baseUrl}}` (must match site).\n\n**Tests:** each request → **Tests** tab. **Rate limits** apply after reCAPTCHA passes.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "https://www.andiamoevents.com" },
    { "key": "recaptchaToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "admin_email", "value": "" },
    { "key": "admin_password", "value": "" },
    { "key": "recaptcha_token", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-m000-4000-8000-000000000001",
      "name": "Manual real login (variables)",
      "description": "Set `admin_email`, `admin_password`, and a fresh `recaptcha_token` from the browser Network tab (see collection description). The POST request uses a Pre-request script to JSON-encode the body. Run POST first, then GET verify-admin.",
      "item": [
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-m001-4000-8000-000000000001",
          "name": "POST admin-login — real credentials",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Origin", "value": "{{baseUrl}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{admin_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{admin_password}}\",\n  \"recaptchaToken\": \"{{recaptcha_token}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin-login",
            "description": "Requires valid `recaptcha_token` from the browser (expires quickly). Use collection Variables; mark `admin_password` as Secret in Postman."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "id": "a1b2c3d4-prm1-4000-8000-000000000001",
                "exec": [
                  "function resolveVar(k) {",
                  "  const nz = (v) => (v !== undefined && v !== null && String(v).trim() !== '' ? String(v) : '');",
                  "  let v = nz(pm.environment.get(k));",
                  "  if (v) return v;",
                  "  v = nz(pm.collectionVariables.get(k));",
                  "  if (v) return v;",
                  "  v = nz(pm.globals.get(k));",
                  "  if (v) return v;",
                  "  try {",
                  "    if (typeof pm.variables !== 'undefined' && pm.variables.get) {",
                  "      v = nz(pm.variables.get(k));",
                  "      if (v) return v;",
                  "    }",
                  "  } catch (e) {}",
                  "  return '';",
                  "}",
                  "let email = resolveVar('admin_email');",
                  "let password = resolveVar('admin_password');",
                  "let recaptchaToken = resolveVar('recaptcha_token');",
                  "try {",
                  "  const raw0 = pm.request && pm.request.body && pm.request.body.raw;",
                  "  if (typeof raw0 === 'string' && raw0.trim().charAt(0) === '{') {",
                  "    const p = JSON.parse(raw0);",
                  "    if (p && typeof p === 'object') {",
                  "      if (!email && p.email != null) email = String(p.email);",
                  "      if (!password && p.password != null) password = String(p.password);",
                  "      if (!recaptchaToken && p.recaptchaToken != null) recaptchaToken = String(p.recaptchaToken);",
                  "    }",
                  "  }",
                  "} catch (e) {}",
                  "pm.request.body.update({",
                  "  mode: 'raw',",
                  "  raw: JSON.stringify({",
                  "    email: email || '',",
                  "    password: password || '',",
                  "    recaptchaToken: recaptchaToken || '',",
                  "  }),",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "id": "a1b2c3d4-sm01-4000-8000-000000000001",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('Login success', () => pm.response.json().success === true);",
                  "  pm.test('Admin object returned', () => !!pm.response.json().admin);",
                  "} else if (pm.response.code === 401) {",
                  "  pm.test('Invalid credentials', () => pm.response.json().error === 'Invalid credentials');",
                  "} else if (pm.response.code === 400) {",
                  "  pm.test('Bad request (often reCAPTCHA)', () => !!pm.response.json().error);",
                  "} else if (pm.response.code === 429) {",
                  "  pm.test('Rate limited', () => true);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  pm.test('Unexpected status ' + pm.response.code, () => false);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "a1b2c3d4-m002-4000-8000-000000000001",
          "name": "GET verify-admin — after login (cookie jar)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Origin", "value": "{{baseUrl}}" }],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/verify-admin",
            "description": "Run **after** a successful POST login. Postman saves `adminToken` from Set-Cookie for this domain."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "id": "a1b2c3d4-sm02-4000-8000-000000000001",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Session valid', () => j.valid === true);",
                  "  pm.test('Has admin', () => !!j.admin);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  pm.test('Not authenticated (run POST login first, or cookie expired)', () => [401, 403].includes(pm.response.code));",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-1001-4000-8000-000000000001",
      "name": "Admin login page",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/login",
        "description": "Assertions are in the **Tests** tab (not visible until you select this request)."
      },
      "response": [],
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "id": "a1b2c3d4-s101-4000-8000-000000000001",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('HTML response', () => (pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type') || '').includes('text/html'));"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-1002-4000-8000-000000000001",
      "name": "POST admin-login — CORS blocked (bad Origin)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Origin", "value": "https://evil.example" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\"email\":\"test@invalid.local\",\"password\":\"wrong\",\"recaptchaToken\":\"x\"}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin-login",
        "description": "See **Tests** tab for assertions."
      },
      "response": [],
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "id": "a1b2c3d4-s102-4000-8000-000000000001",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 403 CORS', () => pm.response.to.have.status(403));",
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('CORS error body', () => j.error && j.error.includes('CORS'));"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
